The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Barzani of the Kurdistan region and Vice President Pence during Pence's visit to Erbil, Iraqi Kurdistan. President Barzani welcomes Vice President Pence and expresses gratitude for the United States' support in the fight against ISIS. Pence thanks President Barzani and discusses the enduring bond between the Kurdish people and the United States. He also expresses gratitude for the Kurdish soldiers and their families who sacrificed in the fight against ISIS. Pence looks forward to discussing ways to strengthen the relationship between the Kurdish region and the United States. Both leaders emphasize the strong bonds between the two nations and their commitment to building a peaceful and prosperous future.